vectorData.altText: 9. Identify the layer indicated by the letter A. Be specific.

Squamous cells with membrane-bound packages of protein forms “soft keratin”, as opposed to the “hard keratin” that forms in hair.
Desmosomes degrade as cells migrate toward surface, therefore keratinized cells shed or desquamated from skin surface.
That's right! Stratum corneum can be identified by the stratified layer of anucleated squamous cells. Remember, keratinocytes shed their organelles in S. granulosum before entering this layer.
